# DemoForge — Project Conventions for AI Agents

## Overview
Turn any website or screenshot into an interactive guided sales demo. Single-page HTML/JS app + Python server. Serves on localhost:9000. Dark theme with cyan accent.

## Sacred Files — NEVER modify without explicit permission
- `index.html` — The entire frontend app. All UI logic and CSS live here.
- `server.py` — Python HTTP backend. Demo storage, share links, proxy.
- `data/` — Live demo JSON storage. Do not delete.

## Test Commands
```bash
# Syntax check
cd ~/Projects/demoforge && python3 -c "import server; print('server imports OK')"

# Start server
cd ~/Projects/demoforge && python3 server.py &
sleep 2 && curl -s http://localhost:8766/api/demos
curl -s -X POST http://localhost:8766/api/demos -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"title":"Test Demo","source":{"type":"image","url":null,"imageData":"data:image/png;base64,test"},"hotspots":[{"pctX":0.5,"pctY":0.5,"text":"Hello world"}]}'
kill %1 2>/dev/null
```

## Architecture
- `index.html` — Single-page app (SPA). Dark UI, landing + capture + editor + player + share screens.
- `server.py` — BaseHTTPRequestHandler backend. Port 8766. Stores demos as JSON, serves frontend, handles `/play/{id}` standalone viewer, POST `/api/demos` to save.
- `data/` — JSON demo files persisted to disk.

## Critical Patterns
- Frontend is self-contained: vanilla JS, no build step, no framework.
- Hotspots store percentage coordinates (pctX, pctY) so they scale with any viewport.
- Share links can be server-stored (`/play/{id}`) or local hash-based (`#play=base64`).
- QR codes are canvas-generated inline (no external libraries).
- URL capture uses iframe sandbox for live sites; image upload works offline.
- All text/markdown uses basic hyphens and ASCII dashes only — no em-dashes or curly quotes in source code or JSON.
